Phytosterols and ezetimibe each reduce intestinal cholesterol absorption by 30-55% but appear to have different mechanisms of action.

 The investigators' hypothesis is that phytosterols and ezetimibe given together will block cholesterol absorption in an additive fashion.

 In a randomized, placebo-controlled crossover trial the effects of placebo, ezetimibe treatment and ezetimibe plus phytosterol treatment will be measured.

